  "prompt": "Which is the best recommended book for CA-CPT?",
  "response": "For preparing for the CA-CPT (Common Proficiency Test), several books are highly recommended. Here are a few that are often suggested by students and educators:\n\n1. **\"CA CPT Study Material by ICAI\"** - The Institute of Chartered Accountants of India (ICAI) provides comprehensive study materials for the CA-CPT exam, which cover all subjects in detail.\n\n2. **\"CA-CPT Exam Guide\" by A. Mukherjee / S. M. Lal / P. C. Tulsian** - This book offers a thorough review of the syllabus with practice questions and solved papers.\n\n3. **\"CPT - Common Proficiency Test\" by Vikas Sethi** - This book covers all topics systematically and includes practice questions for better preparation.\n\n4. **\"Comprehensive Guide to CA-CPT\" by Surbhi Bansal** - This book is known for its clarity and structured approach to the syllabus.\n\n5. **\"CA CPT: A Complete Study Package\" by A. K. Soni** - A well-organized book that covers the entire syllabus with illustrative examples.\n\nAlways make sure to check for the latest editions and additional resources such as question banks, mock tests, and previous years' papers to complement your study. Good luck with your exam preparation!",
